<body style="margin-top: 84px !important">
    <div class="container-fluid">
        <div class="row" id="top">
            <div class="headBG shadow-2-strong carousel-item active">
                <div class="mask" style="background-color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.5);">
                    <div class="d-flex justify-content-center align-items-center">
                        <div class="text-center center">
                            <h2>
                                Protecting your skin Today
                            </h2>
                            <br>
                            <h4>to help avoid Cancer in the Future. </h4>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
    <!-- Section: Design block -->
    <section>
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row d-flex justify-content-center mt-5">
                <div class="col-lg-10">
                    <div class="card mb-2">
                        <div class="card-body p-5">
                            <div class="w3-content w3-display-container">
                                <div class='mySlides'>
                                    <h3 id="what">Why is Ultraviolet radiation (UVR) dangerous?</h3>
                                    <div class="leftB">
                                        <p>UVR is comprised of UVA and UVB rays</p>
                                        <p>UVA can deeply penetrate the skin and cause damages, such as wrinkling or blotchiness. UVA also suppresses our immune system.</p>
                                        <p>UVB penetrates the top layer of the skin and causes sunburn, which could further lead to skin cancer.</p>
                                    </div>
                                    <img src="~/assets/img/skin_uva&uvb.jpg" class="img-fluid centerP" style="width:70%; margin-left:80px;" />
                                    <p class="cite">
                                        Picture retrieved from:
                                        <a href="https://1pgozz2wgm3s1zpozx1y808b-wpengine.netdna-ssl.com/wp-content/uploads/uv-penetration-into-layers-of-the-skin.jpg" target="_blank">
                                            UV penetration into layers of the skin
                                        </a>
                                    </p>
                                </div>

                                <div class='mySlides'>
                                    <h3 id="what">Visible Consequences</h3>
                                    <div class="container">
                                        <div class="row">
                                            <div class="col-sm-7">
                                                <div class="leftB">
                                                    <p>Frequent exposure to intense sunlight could cause premature aging of the skin as it becomes thicker and has wrinkles.</p>
                                                    <p><b>Up to 90%</b> of the visible skin aging changes are caused by the interaction with sunlight. With proper protection from UV radiation, most premature aging of the skin <b>can be avoided</b>.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="col-sm-5">
                                                <br />
                                                <h5>Premature aging of the skin</h5>
                                                <img src="~/assets/img/skin_Prematured_Aging.jpg" class="img-fluid" />
                                                <p class="cite">
                                                    Picture retrieved from:
                                                    <a href="https://cdn1.vectorstock.com/i/1000x1000/89/90/premature-wrinkles-cosmetology-aging-of-the-skin-vector-16238990.jpg" target="_blank">
                                                        Premature aging
                                                    </a>
                                                </p>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="container">
                                        <div class="row">
                                            <div class="col-sm-7">
                                                <div class="leftB">
                                                    <p>If you see unusual skin growths on body areas that are frequently exposed to the sunlight, such as the face, hands, or neck, it could be a sign of skin disorders caused by UVR.</p>
                                                    <p> Those areas could be raised, become red, or have a rough surface and also could <b>increase the risk</b> of having <b>skin cancer</b>.</p>
                                                    <p>In that case, <b>please come and see the doctor as soon as possible</b>.</p>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>

                                            <div class="col-sm-5">
                                                <br /><br />
                                                <h5>Rough skin</h5>
                                                <img src="~/assets/img/skin_rough_skin.jpeg" class="img-fluid" />
                                                <p class="cite">
                                                    Picture retrieved from:
                                                    <a href="https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcSvdmZ1zzuXswU3RsBZG_T8ne1blZqgE9bX_g&usqp=CAU" target="_blank">
                                                        Rough skin
                                                    </a>
                                                </p>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>

                                <div class='mySlides'>
                                    <h3 id="Types">Severe Consequences</h3>
                                    <div class="container">
                                        <div class="row">
                                            <div class="col-md-9">
                                                <div class="leftB">
                                                    <p><b>Melanoma</b> is a type of skin cancer that could be caused by UVR. It is one of the most common cancers <b>among young people aging from 15 to 29</b>. </p>
                                                    <p>UV exposure and sunburns, particularly during childhood, <b>increases the risk</b> of having this disease.</p>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="leftB">
                                                    <p><b>Basal Cell Carcinomas</b> is a type of skin cancer that could be caused by UVR.</p>
                                                    <p>With this condition, <b>small and fleshy bumps</b> would appear on the <b>head or neck</b> before slowly growing larger. Those bumps could <b>penetrate to the bone</b> and cause significant damages.</p>
                                                </div>
                                                <div class="leftB">
                                                    <p><b>Squamous Cell Carcinomas</b> is similar to Basal Cell Carcinomas as red and scaly patches appear and spread on <b>multiple parts of the body</b>.</p>
                                                </div>

                                                <button class="carosel_button" id="gen_button">How UVR damages the DNA</button>
                                                <div id="gen_modal" class="modal">
                                                    <div class="modal-content">
                                                        <span class="close" id="close_gen">&times;</span>
                                                        <p><b>How UVR damages the DNA</b></p>
                                                        <img src="~/assets/img/dna.jpg" alt="First-aid Treatement to sunburn" class="skinPic centerP" style="width:100%;"><br>
                                                        <p class="cite" style="text-align: left;">
                                                            Retrieve from:
                                                            <a href="https://www.cancercouncil.com.au/wp-content/uploads/2020/08/UV-damages-DNA-1024x633.jpg" target="_blank">Statistics on skin cancer in Australia</a>
                                                        </p>
                                                    </div>
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                            <div class="col-md-3">
                                                <img src="~/assets/img/cancerstat.png" alt="First-aid Treatement to sunburn" class="skinPic centerP" style="width:100%;"><br>
                                                <p class="cite" style="text-align: left;">
                                                    Retrieve from:
                                                    <a href="https://vivacommunications.com.au/blog/skin-cancer-fact-sheet-australia/" target="_blank">Statistics on skin cancer in Australia</a>
                                                </p>
                                            </div>
                                        </div>
                                    </div>
                                </div>

                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div id="page_num"></div>
                    <span class="caption text-muted">
                        <button class="carosel_button" onclick="plusDivs(-1)">❮</button>
                        <button class="carosel_button" onclick="plusDivs(1)">❯</button>
                    </span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <script>
        // Get the buttons
        var gen_button = document.getElementById("gen_button");

        // Get the modal
        var gen_modal = document.getElementById("gen_modal");

        // When the user clicks the button, open the modal
        gen_button.onclick = function () {
            gen_modal.style.display = "block";
        }

        var close_gen = document.getElementById("close_gen");
        close_gen.onclick = function () {
            gen_modal.style.display = "none";
        }


        // When the user clicks anywhere outside of the modal, close it
        window.onclick = function (event) {
            if (event.target == gen_modal) {
                gen_modal.style.display = "none";
            }
        }

        // Carosel
        var slideIndex = 1;
        showDivs(slideIndex);

        function plusDivs(n) { showDivs(slideIndex += n); }

        function currentDiv(n) { showDivs(slideIndex = n); }

        function showDivs(n) {
            var i;
            var pagenum = [];
            var x = document.getElementsByClassName("mySlides");
            var dots = document.getElementsByClassName("demo");
            if (n > x.length) { slideIndex = 1 }
            if (n < 1) { slideIndex = x.length }
            for (i = 0; i < x.length; i++) {
                x[i].style.display = "none";
            }
            for (i = 0; i < dots.length; i++) {
                dots[i].className = dots[i].className.replace(" w3-red", "");
            }
            x[slideIndex - 1].style.display = "block";
            pagenum.push(`<p style="text-align:center">Pages: ${slideIndex}/${x.length}</p>`);
            page_num.innerHTML = pagenum.join('');
            dots[slideIndex - 1].className += " w3-red";
        }</script>
</body>

</html>
